This is the strongest white move in this opening,  and black play is not easy.
It needs much knowledge and skill to win here.
In fact, I spent so many hours in analysing black win before.
indeed, looks very logical and safe.

Black will not block the line 2_6,
because it is more important to create its own VCT threat using the h5 connection.
White cannot play actively, so it will try to balance.

This move way be unclear though.
Let me explain.

at first look, we may think that black only created one line, 5_11, while 3_11 is potentially dead
because of white four

but in fact it is not true.
The pair 3_11 is not dead.

Because, if white will block the pair 3_11, it will be replaced with pair h9_i10,
and black is even stronger.
the pair 3_11 did its job by creating the link of h9_i10
And since white is now even worse, so white is forced not to touch the i8 point.
which means both 3_11 and 5_11 are good lines for black.
black does not go to i8 either.

Because of simple rule: if white cannot take i8, why do we need to waste stone there so early, we can go i8 anytime later, right?
so black just played L7
